Osun State Governor Adegboyega Oyetola has disclosed the reasons why the residents want him to be re-elected on July 16. He said his love for the masses, passion for the welfare of the residents and the development of the state were some of the reasons people wanted him to be re-elected.   Adeleke, Babayemi factions agree on delegates ahead PDP…     ‘Ibadan deserves special status’     I will not take my unopposed ticket for granted, says…   Oyetola, represented by his Special Adviser on Civic Engagement, Olatunbosun Oyintiloye, during N30 million fund raising ceremony organised by the Ebira community in Osogbo, yesterday, said: “My decision to seek re-election is due to the confidence reposed in my administration by the electorate, who appreciate my meaningful contributions in the last three and a half years.” He added: “Since the inception of our administration, concerted efforts have been centred on fortifying the security architecture through the establishment of security joint task force to complement the mainstream security agencies in preventing crime in the state.”